1. Vision

MedFabric is an enterprise-grade Healthcare Data & AI Platform designed to demonstrate modern platform engineering, healthcare data engineering, analytics engineering, predictive modeling, governance, and cloud-ready architecture.

The platform transforms raw healthcare data into trusted analytical datasets, population health intelligence, predictive risk scores, and governed data products.

The project is intentionally designed using enterprise software engineering principles so it can evolve from a local development environment to cloud-native deployment with minimal architectural changes.

⸻

2. Guiding Principles

Platform First

MedFabric is a platform—not a collection of scripts.

Every component should be reusable, modular, configurable, and independently testable.

⸻

Configuration Driven

All configurable values shall reside in YAML configuration files.

Python code shall contain business logic only.

Examples include:

* Paths
* Thresholds
* Feature definitions
* Model parameters
* Logging settings
* Validation rules
* Output locations
* Pipeline execution settings

No business configuration shall be hardcoded.

⸻

Governance by Design

Every layer shall generate metadata and quality information.

Governance is a first-class capability, not an afterthought.

⸻

Observability by Design

Every module shall support:

* Structured logging
* Run IDs
* Execution metrics
* Performance statistics
* Error tracking
* Audit information

⸻

Reusability

Common functionality shall exist only once.

Examples include:

* Reading data
* Writing data
* Validation
* Logging
* Metadata generation
* Exception handling
* Storage abstraction

⸻

Cloud Ready

The platform shall execute locally while maintaining a cloud-ready architecture.

Migration to Azure, AWS, or GCP should primarily require configuration and infrastructure changes rather than business logic changes.

⸻

Healthcare Focused

Business capabilities shall align with payer analytics, population health, value-based care, predictive analytics, and healthcare operations.

